title: Isaac Newtons’s CV
text:
Physicist, Mathematician, Cambridge professor.

isaac@applesdofall.org | My wikipedia page



410.446.2849 • sariah.daly.vet@gmail.com • www.linkedin.com/Sariahdaly



I am pursuing a major in Pre-Vet and a certificate in Data Science full-time at Brigham Young University - Idaho. I actively get involved in and alternate between various campus organizations like Ballroom dance, Pre-Vet Society, and Peer Mentoring. Next semester I have been hired to tutor for CHEM 105.



2021 - NOW Brigham Young University - Idaho.

Bachelors of Animal Science: Pre-Vet
Certificate in Data Science

Fall 2024 - NOW BYU-I Pre-Vet Society.

Secretary [Fall 2024]

Fall 2023 Heber J. Grant Peer Mentor.
Spring 2023 - Spring 2024 Ballroom Dance Instructor.

Manager (Spring 2024)




May 2023 – August 2023 Church Camp Counselor, Provo, UT For The Strength of Youth Program – Brigham Young University

Taught material from the provided handbook with inspired changes from related sources
Provided enriching activities and learning to youth to connect with their faith
Communicated with Assistant Coordinators, Coordinators, and other leadership to ensure connection
Exhibited positivity, patience, and flexibility in times of unpredictability and error
Catered to youth’s individual spiritual, physical, and emotional needs

December 2022 – June 2023 Inventory Manager, Rexburg, ID Righteous Slice

Compiled Cost of Goods Sold, Sales, and Labor data into a Prime Cost report for owner
Designed an Excel dashboard to visualize historical, present and future sales data
Created a spreadsheet to track details about each item and ensure standardized training in the future
Tracked inventory in the restaurant to determine what par levels of each item is needed for the week
Communicated with supplier representative to lower prices by 10-20% on more than 20 items
Submit orders to suppliers to achieve lowest price possible while maintaining quality

May 2021 - August 2021 Executive Assistant, Annapolis Junction, MD TurboHaul

Assembled Excel sheets for inventory and led research on collections, earned $895 from selling items in a month
Corresponded with President of the company and communicated with clients about accounts receivable, recovered over $5000 owed to the business
Reconciled and applied payments, performed data entry, organized human resource files for 50+ employees
